FAQs on University Targu Mures Medical Campus Hamburg (UMCH)
What is the University Targu Mures Medical Campus Hamburg (UMCH)?
UMCH is a branch of the University of Medicine, Pharmacy, Science, and Technology of Targu Mures (UMFST) in Romania, located in Hamburg, Germany. It offers high-quality medical education with a focus on combining theoretical knowledge with practical experience.

What programs are offered at UMCH?
UMCH offers a variety of medical programs, including Medicine, Dental Medicine, and other health-related fields. These programs are designed to meet international standards and prepare students for global medical careers.

Are the programs at UMCH taught in English?
Yes, many of the programs at UMCH are taught in English, making them accessible to international students who do not speak German.
